      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "INVICTUS TOMMY (1) has been in the money at his last two runs, most recently when third (17.07) in a Maiden over 300m at Murray Bridge Straight. With a good start should be able to take advantage of the rails draw. Key player on best and expected to bounce back. WILLOW TYSON (5) is a Tony Lagana-trained newcomer by Fernando Bale out of Suzie Rose. No favours with the draw and will need to begin well. Respect any strong moves in the market. CASH CARRIAGE (3) did a good job to finish third last time out over 342m at Angle Park (20.66) in a Maiden, the second top-three finish on the trot. With a good start should be able to take advantage of the low draw. Can turn it around this time. GULF STREAM (7) can run a bold race on best form.",
